Boaz Weinstein’s Hedge Fund Accused of Cheating Investor 
Canadian pension fund says Saba Capital cut value of portfolio before paying redemption request, then marked it back up

 






By

Rob Copeland


Rob Copeland
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyRob Copeland
@realrobcopeland
rob.copeland@wsj.com




  Updated Sept. 27, 2015 7:41 p.m. ET





 Boaz Weinstein, the onetime Deutsche Bank AG trading star who now runs his own hedge-fund firm, was accused in a lawsuit Friday of cheating one of his biggest investors earlier this year when they asked for their money back. Canada’s Public Sector Pension Investment Board alleges that Mr. Weinstein’s Saba Capital Management LP reduced the value of its portfolio right before paying out the redemption request, and then marked the...
  


